I've made this several times and have found that it's better when you make the rice on the side, and then put a healthy spoonful of rice in each bowl and top it with the soup. Otherwise the rice tends to disintegrate by the time the meatballs are done. Also, with the rice you lose the clarity of the broth. As others have said, ground chicken or turkey, turkey sausage, chicken broth, and skim milk work fine.

