This recipe is missing a lot. Real Albondigas have chopped mint in them. THAT'S what people are saying is missing. I would add about 3 tb of finely chopped mint to the recipe. Also, beef broth isn't generally used. I add none. I use 3 cans of hiqh quality canned tomatoes as the basis for the broth, with onion, garlic, a pinch of cumin, and cilantro blended in. I also fry the tomato mixture in a little oil to bring out the flavor for about 10 minutes, then add a bay leaf. I thin it with a little water if it's too thick, but when adding the tomato juice from the cans, you generally don't need it. If you use fresh tomatoes, be sure they're SUPER ripe. The meatballs will add the meaty taste to the broth. Also, the meatballs are never browned, as one person mentioned she did. The addition of rice is generally made at the time of serving or the rice is put in the meatballs, but not just tossed into the broth.

