Rating: 3
I used a lot of the suggestions from the reviews. I used beef base instead of the canned broth. Added a can of Rotel tomatoes and a can of corn. When making meatballs (or meatloaf), I always cook a bit in the microwave to taste for seasoning. This definitely needed something so I added some chorizo and about a tablespoon of chipotle Tabasco. Much better. I forgot to add the cornmeal, but luckily the meatballs stayed together. Personally I don't think this is a quick soup. Unless you want to bring out the food processor, it takes a while to chop all those onions, clean and chop the cilantro and form the meatballs. The soup is so good it is worth the time though.

